name: CPP Modules
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-minishell, ft_services, libasm, and exam-rank-03

name: ft_printf
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-libft
description:
This project is pretty straight forward. You will recode printf.
You will then be allowed to reuse the function in your future projects.
You will mainly learn how to use variadic arguments.

name: get_next_line
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-libft
description: May it be a file, stdin, or even later a network connection, you will always need a way to read content line by line. It is time to start working on this function, which will be essential for your future projects.

name: Libft
description: This project is your very first project as a student at 42. You will need to recode a few functions of the C standard library as well as some other utility functions that you will use during your whole cursus.

name: minishell
rules: You must have validated ft_server and exam-rank-02. You must have validated 1 of cub3d and minirt

name: Philosophers
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-minishell, ft_services, libasm, and exam-rank-03

name: netwhat
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-libft
description:
Netwhat will allow you to discover the network and to understand how it works. This will allow you to understand how some things you already 
use in your everyday life, without even knowing it.
For that you will answer a questionnaire on the website netwhat.42.fr.

name: cub3d
rules: You must not have registered to minirt. You must have validated 42cursus-get_next_line, 42cursus-ft_printf, and netwhat

name: miniRT
rules: You must not have registered to cub3d. You must have validated 42cursus-ft_printf, 42cursus-get_next_line, and netwhat

name: libasm
rules: You must have validated ft_server and exam-rank-02. You must have validated 1 of cub3d and minirt
description: The aim of this project is to get familiar with assembly language.

name: CPP Module 00
rules: You must have validated 42cursus-minishell, libasm, and ft_services
description:
This first module of C++ is designed to help you understand the specifities of the language when compared to C.
Time to dive into Object Oriented Programming!
